    (14,'B312','Contemporary Cross-Cultural Analysis','ANTH','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','An examination of conformity, conflict or stability, of human interactions across cultural boundaries both at home and abroad, the positive and negative consequences of increasing global interconnectedness and the role of culture change, ethnic identity or religious unity in creating contradictory social and political trends. (Satisfies USCB General Education Global Citizenship and Multicultural Understanding Requirement).'),
