    (244,'B450','Modeling and Simulation','CSCI','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','{§ISAT B450} (Prerequisite: CSCI B350 or consent, and STAT B340) An introduction to modeling and simulation. Topics include fundamental techniques in designing, coding, and use of simulation software to represent actual or theoretical systems in order to observe their behavior and evaluate design correctness.'),
    (245,'B502','Numerical Analysis and Computing','CSCI','GR, UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','{§MATH B502} (Prerequisite: CSCI B280 and MATH B240 [or demonstrated equivalent knowledge/experience], or consent of instructor) Application of tools and techniques to algorithmic problems arising in discrete applied math. Topics include probabilistic methods, entropy, linear algebra methods, risk analysis, approximation and optimization techniques, and performance analysis.'),
    (246,'B360','Operating Systems','CSCI','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','(Prerequisite: CSCI B145 or a high-level programming language). Introduction to operating systems. Topics include evolution of operating systems,
