    (247,'B500','Practical Computing for Computational Scientists','CSCI','GR, UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','(Prerequisite: Enrollment in CSCI M.S. program OR consent of instructor) Application of mathematical, science, and engineering problems to software
 engineering. Introduction to operating systems including UNIX/LINUX.'),
    (248,'B601','Principles of Computer Security','CSCI','GR',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','Prerequisite: CSCI B201 [or demonstrated equivalent knowledge/experience] or consent of instructor) Principles and practices of computer system
