    (251,'B104','Software Design and Development','CSCI','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','{§ISAT B104} (Prerequisites: Two years of college preparatory mathematics or equivalent) Students successfully completing this course will have developed basic competence in computer programming techniques, practices, and tools. Topics include: coding standards and best practices; implicit and explicit types; conditional/complex-conditional logic; iteration; logic encapsulation and code modularity; parameter/argument usage; file input and output; Integrated Development Environment (IDE) usage; computer program creation. Previous programming experience is not required.'),
