    (727,'B370','Introduction to Public Administration','POLI','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','A study of the basic principles and theory of administrative structure, responsibility and control in relation to policy making in the modern state.'),
    (728,'B400','Selected Topics in Political Theory','POLI','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','Intensive analysis of a particular topic or topics. To be identified by topic title each semester. May be repeated under different topics.'),
