    (747,'B101','Introduction to Psychology','PSYC','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','An introduction to and survey of the basic concepts and findings within the field of psychology.'),
    (748,'B203','Laboratory in Psychology','PSYC','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','(Prerequisite: PSYC B200, PSYC B201 and STAT B201 or PSYC B202) Laboratory in psychology in which research methods and statistical methods are integrated. One lecture and one laboratory session per week.'),
    (749,'B302','Learning and Memory','PSYC','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','(Prerequisite: PSYC B101) Research and applications concerning the acquisition of new behavior and knowledge, including accounts based on classical and instrumental conditioning and on information-processing models.'),
