    (770,'B101','Basic Health','PUBH','UG',4,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','This course is a basic health course in which students will learn about strategies to improve health. Nutrition, fitness, drugs, and sexuality are some of
 the topics discussed. Career opportunities within the health field will be explored.'),
    (771,'B390','Field Experience in Public Health','PUBH','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','(Prerequisite: PUBH B310 and Junior Status) A period of introductory work-related education that allows students to reinforce classroom learning while gaining practical experience in a supervised setting where public health principles are applied.'),
    (772,'B321','Fundamentals of Occupational Health & Safety','PUBH','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','(Prerequisite: PUBH B310) An introductory course covering major issues in occupational health and safety, with an emphasis on the identification,
