    (777,'B315','Health Promotion Across the Lifespan','PUBH','UG',4,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','(Prerequisite: PSYC B209 or PSYC B321) The study of age as a determinant of health and disease outcomes across the lifespan with strategies to promote wellness.'),
    (778,'B399','Independent Study in Public Health','PUBH','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','(Prerequisite: PUBH B310 or consent of instructor) This course examines concepts, emerging trends, issues, and evidence-based practice changes in public health practice. Variable hours between 1 to 4 credits, depending on topic which may include complementary and alternative health practices, working with special populations, emerging public health needs, etc. Students may re-take one additional time for a maximum of 8 credits.'),
    (779,'B480','Internship in Public Health','PUBH','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','(Prerequisite: PUBH B450; Co-requisite: PUBH B460) A period of work-related education that allows students to reinforce classroom learning while
