    (780,'B340','Introduction to Environmental Health','PUBH','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','(Prerequisite: PUBH B310) The study of environmental factors, be they physical, chemical, biological or behavioral that have the potential to adversely impact human and/or ecological health.'),
    (781,'B310','Introduction to Public Health','PUBH','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','A broad-based overview of those processes that enable people to assume responsibility for health and wellness and the role of the public health
