    (811,'B309','Introduction to Social Inequality','SOCY','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','This course applies a sociological framework to understand social stratification and inequality. Students will learn major sociology paradigms or metatheories of the relationship of society to the individual and will apply them in the empirical analysis of social inequality.'),
    (812,'B340','Introduction to Social Problems','SOCY','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','Normative dissensus and behavioral deviance in society and their consequences for social change and social order. Problems may include: mental
 disorders, juvenile delinquency, crime, drug abuse, alcoholism, suicide, sexual pathology, race and ethnic relations, world population crises and work
 problems.'),
    (813,'B101','Introductory Sociology','SOCY','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','An introduction to sociological facts and principles: an analysis of group-making processes and products.'),
    (814,'B355','Minority Group Relations','SOCY','UG',3,'University Of South Carolina Beaufort','Theories, methods and substantive issues in the study of majority-minority group relations and social processes and cultural orientations associated
